cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.HC

The paper focuses on developing software to improve users' security and privacy on online social networks, specifically Facebook. This falls under the category of social networking and information systems (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the identification of fake profiles, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and computer networks and communications (cs.CR). The use of machine learning techniques to develop classifiers could also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses users' privacy settings and the number of applications installed on Facebook profiles, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
